Police are investigating a case of murder after four unknown gunmen chased a man inside a Durban shopping mall and shot him dead. The incident happened on Sunday evening at Berea Centre, in Durban. Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, KwaZulu-Natal provincial police spokesperson, said two men had just parked their car near a hair salon on King Dinizulu Road when they were accosted by four gunmen who opened fire at them. “The complainant drove off whilst his friend ran into a nearby shopping centre. The suspects followed the victim into the shopping centre and shot him four times in the abdomen,” said Gwala on Monday morning. Gwala said the 29-year-old man was declared dead on the scene. Charges of murder and attempted murder were opened at Umbilo police station.